And it has been in the past, and we're saying that the church we choose to be is that in the future.

38:06.666 --> 38:12.876
That when people walk in, we don't want them to feel like we are a church full of perfect Christians who all are having together.

38:13.357 --> 38:17.463
But we also don't want them to feel like we're a church full of people who just say the right things.

38:17.744 --> 38:24.114
When people interact with us, we want them to feel the presence of God through how we live.

38:24.866 --> 38:29.459
not just do what we say, not just do what we post, not just do what we sample.

38:29.679 --> 38:32.286
It's not enough to just say I believe in the Word of God.

38:32.567 --> 38:35.576
I want to live like I believe in the Word of God.

38:35.596 --> 38:37.340
And that's the church that we choose to be.

38:39.787 --> 38:40.850
So I'm gonna pray for us.

38:41.730 --> 38:45.934
I'll tell you this, and after I pray at all of our campuses, we have an area called the Next Step Center.

38:45.954 --> 38:48.936
If you're here at Sugar Land, it's right out here to the doors on my right.

38:48.956 --> 38:50.878
There's a glass wall you walk right in there.

38:50.898 --> 38:56.843
If you want to give your life to Christ today, maybe you're realizing, hey, I've been in church all my life, and I've never truly been a Christian.

38:56.883 --> 39:01.707
If you want to give your life to Christ today as soon as we dismiss, you can go right out those doors to the Next Step Center.

39:01.727 --> 39:05.290
And even if you're at Missouri City, it'll be on your right side.

39:05.310 --> 39:07.312
You'll stand up your head right out those doors to the right.

39:07.352 --> 39:08.653
It's along that glass wall.

39:08.673 --> 39:11.716
You see the Next Step Center there, and people are already there to pray with you.

39:11.696 --> 39:15.601
and talk you through whatever it is that you are going through right now.

39:16.062 --> 39:16.903
And here's the last one.

39:16.923 --> 39:22.270
Maybe you're in the room and there's a sin in your heart that you're just like, hey, I just need to confess this and I need somebody to pray with me.

39:22.490 --> 39:24.633
You can go to the next step center today.

39:24.894 --> 39:29.580
And again, let me tell you who you're gonna find when you get over there at every campus in any language, in any service.

39:29.600 --> 39:33.145
You're not gonna find anybody who feels like they're perfect.

39:33.165 --> 39:37.390
You're not gonna find anybody who gets this right 100% of the time.

39:37.410 --> 39:40.114
But you'll find people who have dedicated their lives.

39:40.514 --> 39:46.041
to even in the moment I make mistakes, I repent and seek the Lord to try to do what He asked me to do.

39:47.383 --> 39:48.404
So let me pray for His church.

39:49.745 --> 39:54.271
Father, thank You, thank You, thank You for this day that You have given us.

39:55.092 --> 40:01.440
I pray, God, that we will be a church of people who choose to live out what we say we believe.

40:02.141 --> 40:05.065
God, we want to follow You in word and in action.

40:05.866 --> 40:09.490
And God, we genuinely just want to be the people You've called us to be.

40:09.634 --> 40:17.069
So God let it be that when people interact with somebody from Sugar Creek Baptist Church, that they see people who have an unwavering commitment to God's Word.

40:17.730 --> 40:21.658
And in that unwavering commitment, that they live out what they say they believe.

40:22.399 --> 40:24.183
It's in Jesus' name we pray.

40:24.223 --> 40:25.024
Everybody together say it.

40:26.066 --> 40:26.387
Amen.

40:26.407 --> 40:27.890
Come on church, can we clap our hands?

